args: Is everything all right, my boy?\nI see you're still holed up in here.
It'd be a shame to waste a fine costume,\nso why not go out and enjoy the party?
I'm only participating in this tomfoolery\nso I can learn more about the healing\naromatic. I cannot allow myself to get—
I thought I said you needed to ENJOY\nHalloween in order to understand.
Well, yes. You did. But, um...
You have no idea how to enjoy this\nholiday, do you?
Perhaps you should start by participating\nin a little prank or two.
I am no child, Doctor, and pranks are not\nthe sort of thing someone my age should—
SNEAK ATTACK! HA HA HA HA!
Owww... C'mon, man, don't DODGE me!\nThat's totally against the rules!
Anyone would dodge rather than subject\nthemselves to one of your tricks.
Ha! Guess you ARE pretty used to this\nby now, huh, Sylas?
How many years do you think I've had to\nput up with pranks from the pair of you?
But in that case, why not come out and\npull a couple prank-a-roos with us?!
Give up, Luca. Ol' Sylas here is stubborn\nas a mule in a molasses plant, so let's\nfall back and call another strategy sesh!
Roger that. And next time, we're gonna\nprank you good!
You see? There are some folks your age\nwho retain an interest in ＂tomfoolery.＂
Ugh. You never know when they'll show up\nwith their horseplay.
You mean the hand with paint on it?
Were you attempting to startle me?
If I'm not mistaken, there are more of\nthese pranks popping up than ever.
Well, it IS Halloween. Also, you have a\nterrible reaction to these sorts of things.
That's because I constantly had to suffer\nthough this nonsense when I was young.
From those two who came at you with\nthat smoke-screened knee buckling?\nYou grew up with them, I take it?
Doctor, I have to ask: How can pranking\nhave anything whatsoever to do with the\nessence of a healing aromatic?
Perhaps you will understand if you\nproperly face those who wish to prank you.
I think you should start by talking with\nthese children here.
Well, that was less than helpful. ...Hmm?
There's a white ball rolling this way.\nDid somebody drop it?
Pssst! Look! He's gonna pick it up!
I take it you are the owner of this?
Ha ha ha! Guess the cat's outta the bag.\nBut you were pretty surprised, huh, mister?
Yes, it is a quite a fine replica\nof the human eyeball.
No. I was merely acting in an attempt to\nlure out the prankster. And here you are.
Man, I knew pranking you was gonna\nbe tough, but sheesh!
Everyone's sayin' that you're super tough\nto prank because not even Luca can get\na good reaction out of you.
So we're having a contest to see\nwho can get you to react first!
Ah, I see. That explains why these pranks\nhave been increasing in number.
More importantly, have we met before?
Yeah! When I was sick, you helped me\nget better with your smell thingies!
Ah, now I remember! I barely recognized\nyou, looking so hale and hearty.
It gladdens me to see you well enough\nto fool around like this.
All because of you, mister! I wanted to be\nsure and show you how much better I got.
And I thank you for it.
A word of advice though, if I may:\nIf you are attempting to prank someone,\nyou must learn to stay quiet.
Now then, here's a treat. Please enjoy\nyour Halloween to the fullest.
Talking to that little scamp helped you\nsee why they wanted to prank you, yes?
It did—but I fail to understand how it\nwill bring me any closer to crafting\nthe healing aromatic.
Sounds like someone still hasn't enjoyed\nhimself to the fullest. Better move on to\nthe next kind, then!
Wait a moment! The next kind of what?!
(Is ANY of this actually going to help me?)
